---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import CareerField from '../components/v23/CareerField.astro';
import ClaimsRun from '../components/v23/ClaimsRun.astro';
import ProjectWorkbench from '../components/v23/ProjectWorkbench.astro';
import { profile } from '../data/profile';
import { publicImpactClaims } from '../data/impactClaims';
import { professionalCases, selectedEngagements, v23Identity } from '../data/v23';
import { recognition } from '../data/recognition';
const impactOrder=['claims-handling','backlog','closure','fwa','p4p'];
const impact=impactOrder.map((id)=>publicImpactClaims.find((claim)=>claim.id===id)).filter(Boolean);
---
<Layout title="Shailesh Dudala — Senior Applied AI / ML Engineer" description="Senior Applied AI / ML Engineer across production agentic AI, predictive healthcare, document intelligence, MLOps, and scientific computing." canonicalPath="/">
  <section class="v23-home-hero">
    <div class="v23-ambient" aria-hidden="true"><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
    <div class="shell v23-hero-grid">
      <div class="v23-hero-copy"><p class="v23-kicker">{v23Identity.name} / {v23Identity.role}</p><h1>Intelligent systems, <em>after the demo.</em></h1><p class="v23-hero-thesis">{v23Identity.thesis}</p><p class="v23-supporting-line">{v23Identity.supportingLine}</p><div class="v23-hero-proof"><span><strong>7+ years</strong> healthcare + insurance</span><span><strong>4 flagship systems</strong> professional, public-safe cases</span><span><strong>7K · 20% · 18%</strong> governed workflow outcomes</span></div><div class="v23-actions"><a class="v23-button primary" href="/work/">Explore professional work <span>↗</span></a><a class="v23-button ghost" href="/experience/">Follow the career arc <span>↓</span></a></div><div class="v23-social"><a href={profile.github}>GitHub ↗</a><a href={profile.linkedin}>LinkedIn ↗</a><a href="/resume/">Public résumé ↗</a></div></div>
      <div class="v23-hero-instrument" aria-label="From uncertain signal to bounded action"><div class="instrument-orb"><span>SYSTEM / ONLINE</span><strong>Uncertain signal</strong><i></i><i></i><i></i><b>bounded<br/>action</b></div><ol>{['Observe','Predict','Deliver','Assemble context','Act','Review'].map((step,index)=><li class:list={{active:index===4,authority:index===5}}><span>{String(index+1).padStart(2,'0')}</span><strong>{step}</strong></li>)}</ol><p><span>CURRENT FRONTIER / 2026</span><strong>Production claims and document agents</strong><small>Typed state · tools · validation · exceptions · human authority</small></p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="shell v23-first-read"><div><span>ROLE</span><strong>Senior Applied AI / ML Engineer</strong></div><div><span>ARC</span><strong>Scientific computing → predictive ML → agentic AI</strong></div><div><span>OUTCOMES</span><strong>7K backlog · 20% closure · 18% waste</strong></div><div><span>EVIDENCE</span><strong>4 professional cases · 39 authored repositories</strong></div></div>
  </section>

  <section class="v23-decision-gate" aria-labelledby="decision-gate-title"><div class="shell"><header><p class="v23-kicker">HIRING DECISION / THREE FLAGSHIP PROBLEMS</p><h2 id="decision-gate-title">The problem, the system decision, the documented change.</h2></header><div>{professionalCases.slice(0,3).map((item)=><article><span>{item.number} / {item.eyebrow}</span><h3>{item.title}</h3><p>{item.lede}</p><strong>{item.proof}</strong><a href={item.href}>Inspect the case <span>↗</span></a></article>)}</div><aside><p><strong>Role fit:</strong> senior applied AI / ML engineering across consequential workflows, product delivery, and accountable model operations.</p><nav aria-label="Hiring decision links"><a class="v23-button primary" href="/resume/">Open public résumé <span>↗</span></a><a class="v23-button ghost" href={`mailto:${profile.email}`}>Start a conversation <span>↗</span></a></nav></aside></div></section>

  <section class="v23-section career-section"><div class="shell v23-section-heading"><div><p class="v23-kicker">01 / Career breadth</p><h2>The current work is stronger because of the systems that came before it.</h2></div><p>Scientific rigor became predictive healthcare, then product and MLOps, private document intelligence, and production agentic AI. Zoom out for continuity; zoom in for evidence.</p></div><div class="shell"><CareerField compact /></div></section>

  <section class="v23-section frontier-section"><div class="shell v23-section-heading"><div><p class="v23-kicker">02 / Current frontier</p><h2>An agent is a workflow with authority boundaries—not a prompt with tools.</h2></div><p>Current professional work focuses on claims and document automation. The public reconstruction shows the control architecture without exposing employer data, rules, or systems.</p></div><div class="shell"><ClaimsRun /></div></section>

  <section class="v23-section professional-work-section"><div class="shell v23-section-heading"><div><p class="v23-kicker">03 / Professional work</p><h2>Four systems. Four different uncertainty structures.</h2></div><p>Each case starts with the operating problem and follows the model into validation, delivery, human review, and measurable change.</p></div><div class="shell v23-case-editorial">{professionalCases.map((item)=><article class={`case-editorial-item accent-${item.accent}`}><div class="case-index"><span>{item.number}</span><small>{item.eyebrow}</small></div><div class="case-copy"><h3>{item.title}</h3><p>{item.lede}</p><ol>{item.system.map((step)=><li>{step}</li>)}</ol><a href={item.href}>Open deep case study <span>↗</span></a></div><aside><span>DOCUMENTED CHANGE</span><strong>{item.proof}</strong><p>{item.secondaryProof}</p></aside></article>)}</div><div class="shell v23-section-cta"><a href="/work/">View Work, selected engagements, and capability proof <span>→</span></a></div></section>

  <section class="v23-section impact-section"><div class="shell v23-section-heading compact"><div><p class="v23-kicker">04 / Impact with context</p><h2>Measures stay attached to their workstreams.</h2></div><p>Grounded in the governed career record, public-safe, and qualified where scope matters.</p></div><div class="shell v23-impact-ribbon">{impact.map((claim)=>claim&&<article><span>{claim.context}</span><strong>{claim.value}</strong><h3>{claim.label}</h3>{claim.qualification&&<p>{claim.qualification}</p>}</article>)}</div></section>

  <section class="v23-section engagements-section"><div class="shell v23-section-heading"><div><p class="v23-kicker">05 / Selected engagements</p><h2>Depth beyond the four flagships.</h2></div><p>Quality evidence, FWA, hospital analytics, provider data, and interoperability restore the breadth that a case-study-only portfolio can hide.</p></div><div class="shell engagement-ledger">{selectedEngagements.map((item,index)=><article><span>{String(index+1).padStart(2,'0')}</span><div><small>{item.context}</small><h3>{item.title}</h3></div><strong>{item.result}</strong><p>{item.capabilities.join(' · ')}</p></article>)}</div></section>

  <section class="v23-section project-preview-section"><div class="shell v23-section-heading"><div><p class="v23-kicker">06 / Project Lab</p><h2>Open-source proof without flattening every repository into a success story.</h2></div><p>Inspect architecture, health, evidence, and limits. Featured projects are secondary to professional work and explicit about maturity.</p></div><div class="shell"><ProjectWorkbench compact /></div><div class="shell v23-section-cta"><a href="/lab/">Enter the complete Project Lab <span>→</span></a></div></section>

  <section class="v23-section research-preview-section"><div class="shell research-preview-grid"><div><p class="v23-kicker">07 / Research</p><h2>The ideas behind the work.</h2><p>A curated path from calibrated predictive models and clinical quality to retrieval, agent loops, and representation engineering.</p><a class="v23-button ghost" href="/research/">Open Research <span>↗</span></a></div><div class="research-paths"><a href="/research/#predictive"><span>PATH 01</span><strong>Predictive ML</strong><small>Calibration · explainability · clinical-model quality</small></a><a href="/research/#retrieval"><span>PATH 02</span><strong>Retrieval + agents</strong><small>RAG · tool use · evaluation · authority</small></a><a href="/research/#behavior"><span>PATH 03</span><strong>Model behavior</strong><small>Representations · steering · reproducibility</small></a></div></div></section>

  <section class="v23-section human-section"><div class="shell human-v23-grid"><div><p class="v23-kicker">08 / Human story</p><h2>Ambiguity is where the work begins.</h2></div><div><p>Biomedical informatics taught me that technically correct output can still fail when lineage, assumptions, and operating context are invisible.</p><p>That lesson now shapes how I lead across models, products, documents, agents, and the people accountable for the decision.</p><div><a href="/about/">About and working principles ↗</a><a href="/experience/">Complete experience ↗</a></div></div></div></section>

  <section class="v23-section recognition-preview"><div class="shell"><div><p class="v23-kicker">09 / Recognition</p><h2>Official proof. Team credit intact.</h2></div><div>{recognition.slice(0,3).map((item)=><article><span>{item.attribution}</span><strong>{item.title}</strong><small>{item.project}</small></article>)}</div><a href="/recognition/">View recognition and source notes ↗</a></div></section>

  <section class="v23-contact"><div class="shell"><p class="v23-kicker">10 / Contact</p><h2>Building an AI system where a model output has to become a defensible action?</h2><p>I work across the architecture between those two points.</p><div><a class="v23-button primary" href={`mailto:${profile.email}`}>Email Shailesh <span>↗</span></a><a href={profile.linkedin}>LinkedIn ↗</a><a href={profile.github}>GitHub ↗</a><a href="/resume/">Public résumé ↗</a></div></div></section>
</Layout>
